<item>
            <title>[LU-20103] sanityn nrs_write_read execvp fails running declare</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20103</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Getting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
running as uid/gid/euid/egid 500/500/500/500, groups: 500
[declare] [-a] [pids_r]
execvp fails running declare
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;when running sanityn test_77k. Other sanityn tests that use &lt;tt&gt;nrs_write_read&lt;/tt&gt; should have the same issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;execvp&lt;/tt&gt; treats &lt;tt&gt;declare&lt;/tt&gt; as a executable while it is actually a bash builtin cmd. Will put up a fix soon.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
